	<p>My name is Tip ten Brink / Mijn naam is Tip ten Brink (Dutch below). I was born April 5th, 2000 in the city of Amsterdam, in my home country of the Netherlands. Today, I am a student at the Delft University of Technology (TU Delft), where I recently received my double BSc degree in Applied Mathematics and Applied Physics. Currently, I am pursuing my MSc in Computer Science. I also live in Delft.</p>

	<p>In 2003, I moved to Chicago, in the United States. I returned to the Netherlands in 2006, moving to Baarn. I only left Baarn when I started studying in 2018.</p>

	<p>The coronavirus pandemic caused me to incur some study delay. To still remain busy, I worked part-time as a Shopper (warehouse employee) at Picnic, an online supermarket. Since 2018 I have provided exam training (for final-year high school students) at Stichting Studiebegeleiding Leiden for multiple weekends per year.</p>

	<p>I like to spend my free time on many things. As can be gathered from the topics of this website, I am very interested in technology, politics, math, space, and any kind of other science. I love learning facts. I used to be active at the Jonge Democraten, the (independent) youth wing of D66, the main social-liberal party in the Netherlands.</p>

	<p>I also enjoy programming, reading and writing. The latter mostly involves worldbuilding, details of which I like to share occasionally. I enjoy watching many kinds of sports and personally also like cycling. I occasionally run as well. I love watching movies and I like my TV shows too, maybe I'll share some tips one day. I also play sports, I am active at the Delft track and field student association, D.S.A.V. Dodeka.</p>

